    {
      "type": "articles",
      "specificArticles": [
        {
          "textContent": "From Casa Petri yard you will notice the view to the 'Cârnic' mountain. It’s a mountain of gold, from all points of views, as it hides many tons of gold, but also the unique Roman galleries (some Antiques). On the top of the mountain you will notice a horse-shaped rock, with a cross on top of it. This is the Sphinx or 'Căluțul', our main objective for this trail. Head towards 'Brazi' Lake and 'Platoul Cârnic' (Cârnic Plateau) and then climb through the pine forest to the top of the mountain at the Raven Stone and Sphinx. Return back to the historic center by the Piatra Despicată and Cetate open pit. The Raven Stone and Sphinx can be visited only by foot. The trail is on unpaved roads and is perfect for hiking or mountain bikes.",
